Package SyntSpec

Class SSCarps

java.lang.Object
SyntSpec.SSCarps
Direct Known Subclasses:
ASCarps, FLCarps, GDCarps, SSFLCarps, SSGenomeCarps
public class SSCarps extends Object
SSCarps represents the most basic form of fish. Fish that are SS, or have the value "isSS" as TRUE, are sterile.

      newName - identifying ID tag for the fish
      newAge - fish age, in integer years
      length - input length in cm
      newLocation - SSLake, the current location of the fish
      bornLake - SSLake, the lake the fish was born in
      dispersal - SSLake, used for migration
      ss - TRUE if fish is sterile
      fgender - gender of the fish

    • isMature

      public boolean isMature()
      Return whether the current fish is large enough to reproduce. Fish longer than 360cm are guaranteed to be mature, fish under 330cm are guaranteed to be immature, and in between these values there is an intermediate probability of maturity.
      Returns:
      if a random double invalid input: '<' reproductive function

    • juvenileSurvival

      public int juvenileSurvival()
      Get the number of juveniles that would survive from a single mother's brood. Maximum value (for an empty lake) is 838, and if density is greater than 605, no offspring will survive.
      Returns:
      number of juveniles that will survive from a single brood
